review_blob: Reminds me of a lambic, but slightly less sour.  The first bottle I had tasted cherry-ish, but the second one was more apple-y.
I had the 2007 version. It was thick and oily with no head and no lacing.  Strong coffee and chocolate flavors with a good amount of sweetness/fruitiness.
beer_name: Three Floyds Dark Lord Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: Had it on tap at the York in LA. A very nice hefeweizen- I had it with a lemon squeezed in it. Appropriately cloudy and sweet without being cloying.

We had it at a French bistro under the name Koningshoeven Quadrupel.  Roasty, caramel flavor with a lighter body. The food I was eating took center stage (it was delicious) and overshadowed my experience with this beer.  Ill have to give it another try before adequately rating it.
More hop than I expected.  Complex and spicy, nice finish (though sharp and a bit bitter).
Very nice- rich and tasty, but with its own flavor.  Strikes a nice balance of chocolate/coffee/nutty flavors.
I havent tried it when its actually winter yet, but it tasted great yesterday. I definitely prefer this to Skinny Dip, their summer seasonal.

I loved it because the bitterness that IPA freaks seem to get off on was balanced by the raisin flavor that reminded me of Dogfish Heads Raison Detre.  So imagine that with some extra complexity and kick.
only had a sample at the brewery, but it was very tasty and Id like to try more...

interesting cream ale- nice caramel flavor with vanilla aroma.  a bit inconsistent, though- the first time I had it the mouthfeel was almost like a root beer float, but the next time it was much thinner.
beer_name: Anderson Valley Summer Solstice Cerveza Crema

review_blob: The hazlenut of this beer gets you at the finish, which is smooth and pleasant.  Beautiful color and head.
Nice, malty beer with a bitter finish.  Caramel color with an accordingly off-white head.  Good beer, but not in my list of favorites.
